Karsan Otomotiv, Vestel Elektronik: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-05-04T06:37:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/karsan-otomotiv-vestel-elektronik-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active in
Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the last
close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  rose 549.60, or
0.8 percent, to 70,072.02 yesterday, the highest close since
Nov. 11.  Karsan Otomotiv Sanayii & Ticaret AS (KARSN TI): The
Turkish carmaker failed in a bid to supply New York’s next fleet
of yellow taxi cabs. Nissan Motor Co., Japan’s second-biggest
carmaker, was chosen, Mayor  Michael Bloomberg  said yesterday.
Karsan will continue with a plan to sell its taxi model globally
after losing the auction, it said in a statement to the  Istanbul
Stock Exchange  today. The stock fell for a fifth day, losing 6
kurus, or 2.9 percent to 2 liras.  Vestel Elektronik Sanayi & Ticaret AS (VESTL TI): The
Turkish manufacturer of televisions, personal computers and
monitors, aims to sell 1 million Internet-Connected televisions
in  Europe  this year, Haberturk reported, citing Turan Erdogan,
Vestel Group’s deputy chief executive officer. Vestel also
expects to sell 1.5 million set-top boxes in Europe this year,
compared with 800,000 in 2010, Erdogan said, according to the
Istanbul-based newspaper. Vestel Elektronik rose 1 kurus, or 0.4
percent, to 2.73 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
